{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dfeef866-037d-42cb-9844-d400b2762451","content":"It's a simple change. In your project file, either **remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property or set it to `false`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+** defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so removing `UseVSTest` is all you need.\n2. **CLI changes** — run tests with `dotnet test` as before, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) or use `dotnet test --help` to see new options.\n3. **If you use `.runsettings`** — most settings carry over, but review for any VSTest-specific configuration.\n4. **Extensions** — replace any `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestPlatform.*` packages with their `Microsoft.Testing.*` equivalents if applicable.\n5. **CI/CD** — ensure your pipelines don't rely on VSTest-specific flags (e.g., `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` with the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aae451cb-b332-4a0d-a31d-4db45da23d0b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant content. Let me answer from my knowledge about MSTest.Sdk and the migration from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":371,"requestId":"7031:39211A:DB51CC3:F18DADF:69F2A87E"},"id":"b6667960-0086-4439-9f96-8dc3c3609c00","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:55:36.330Z","parentId":"e955ca44-5a9f-437c-bda9-785b4b6a9bf2"}
